Ramgate Security


* Privilege model

  - Same-user only: signals only processes owned by the invoking user.
    No sudo, no root install.  The LaunchAgent runs in the user session.
  - ram-xray is inert: it sends no signals, mutates no state, and never
    sources lib/guard/.
  - Offline: no network calls.  AI commit assist is local-first and
    opt-in.


* Threat vectors and defenses

  Tampered ramgate.conf (steer the killer, inject code):
    whitelist-parsed, never sourced; unknown keys ignored; malformed
    values fall back to defaults; the file is refused if it is
    group- or world-writable, or not self-owned.

  Crafted process name or command line:
    metadata is data -- quoted literal comparison, never eval, never
    widens a glob.

  Tampered config/hooks/ai.env (HOOKS_AI_CMD is executed):
    a trusted developer-owned file, written by the setup wizard with
    printf %q, and gitignored.

  Guard targets itself or the terminal:
    the protect set is derived at runtime -- kernel_task, launchd,
    WindowServer, Finder/Dock, terminal/tmux/shell, and ram-guard's own
    binary.

  Stray real signal from tests:
    a single signal path in lib/guard/breaker.bash, with an injectable
    seam; tests capture would-be signals.

  Committed secrets:
    the gitleaks pre-commit scan blocks on a hit; ai.env is gitignored.


* Reporting

  Report privately via GitHub Security Advisories (the repository
  Security tab).  Include a description, the affected version
  (ram-xray --version / ram-guard --version), the macOS version, and a
  minimal reproduction.

  Please do not open public issues for unfixed vulnerabilities.
